

Procedure to run the general code

The spatial_simulation_Patung contains all the necessary directories and script in order to rerun all the simulations in a super computer written in Condor (version > 9.0). In particular this code runs on the Patung (SuperComputer) of the LANCIS, Instituto de EcologÃ­a, UNAM. 

The directory contains:

codeMatrizSim.py
creator_CI_patung.py
creator_SubmitFile.py
__init__.py 



------------------------------------------------------------
PROCEDURE [we suppose here that you have already an account in the super Computer and the some specific procedure might change depending on your superComputer requirements.]

----------------------------------------------------------

0. Enter to the terminal in your computer and push the codes from your directories to the supercomputer:

"PATH/subidaPatung_fullLattice" is the path to the directory in your computer where you keep the script.
"sim_fullLattice" is the file in the supercomputer where you will arrange all the files. 

scp -r /PATH/subidaPatung_fullLattice emilio@patung.lancis.ecologia.unam.mx:/srv/home/emilio/sim_fullLattice/

[This will ask you your superComputer accout password]

----------------------------------------------------------
1. Enter the supercomputer Patung (or another supercomputer that runs on Condor >9.0. 
2. Create and environment and install all the necessary modules:

2.1 Install and activate the environment:
sudo install virtualenv
python 3 -m venv mienv
source myenv/bin/activate

2.2. Install all necessary libraries:
sudo install matplotlib
sudo install numpy ...

3. Change the main code (codeMatrizSim) to executable mode. 

chmod +x codigo**.py

4. Create the receptory directories and intial files
4.1. Directories: bitacora, salida and initialConditions

mkdir bitacora salida initialConditions
cd salida/
mkdir dfPicos dfPromedios matricesGenerales

4.2. Fill the initialConditions directory with the different initial conditions
python3 creator_CI_patung.py


4.3. List all the files inside the initialConditions in order to have a text file only with the names:
dir initialConditions/  > listCI.txt

NOTE: In the case of the sensibility analysis or the size Step analysis reported in the supplementary 1, we have to comment or uncomment the parameters that we want to vary and create a listCI.txt for each case. (We can then merge the files if we want to run them all at once). 

4.4. Create the .nwg directory and move the __init__.py inside it

mkdir nwg
mv __init__.py ./nwg/

5. Create the submit file
python3 creator_SubmitFile.py 

-------------------------------------------------------------
Your directory now should contain the following directories an files:

codeMatrizSim.py (activated)
creator_CI_patung.py
creator_SubmitFile.py
__init__.py 
bitacora
salida
salida/dfPromedios
salida/dfPicos
salida/matricesGenerales
initialConditions
listCI.txt
submit_file_fullLattice.sub
.nwg
.nwg/__init__.py

6. Run the submit file in the condor computer

condor_submit submit_file_fullLattice.sub

The bitacora directory keeps track of the possible errors and messages. To see how the jobs are beeing submitted check:

condor_q

If everything runs correctly the dfOnePlant, matrizOnePlant should have the final files that will be used in order to plot the different figures. The bicatora directory keeps track of the different problems or messages during the simulations (.out, .log and .err) 

--------------------------------------------------

7. Exit the superComputer and from your terminal, download produced files in "salida" to your computer, to produce the different figures. 

NOTE: In the case of the sensibility analysis or the size Step analysis reported in the supplementary 1, we ran different times the same simulation changing the creator_CI_patung.py and downloaded the results in different directories:

For the main figures:
scp -r emilio@patung.lancis.ecologia.unam.mx:/srv/home/emilio/sim_fullLattice/salida "PATH"/FiguresCodes/bajadaPatung/

For the Sensitivity analysis:*

scp -r emilio@patung.lancis.ecologia.unam.mx:/srv/home/emilio/sim_fullLattice/salida "PATH"/SupplementaryFigures/FiguresCodes_sems/bajadaPatung_sens/

For the Euler (sizeStep analysis):

scp -r emilio@patung.lancis.ecologia.unam.mx:/srv/home/emilio/sim_fullLattice/salida "PATH"/SupplementaryFigures/FiguresCodes/bajadaPatung_eul/


